    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available for acquisition is a 2004 BMW M3 (E46) featuring the high-revving S54 3.2L inline-six engine equipped with individual throttle bodies and a dual-VANOS variable valve timing system. This example utilizes the preferred Getrag 420G 6-speed manual gearbox, delivering torque to the rear wheels via a factory limited-slip differential. The chassis remains structurally sound with a recent subframe reinforcement and a full cooling system overhaul including a high-flow water pump. Maintenance is up to date, featuring a recent valve shim adjustment and rod bearing inspection. While the exterior shows minor road-derived character, the mechanical synchronization and throttle response remain razor-sharp. Ideal for the purist seeking a visceral, analog driving experience without the premium of a museum-grade specimen.",
